The main fates of IDL involve its uptake by the liver—either via LDL receptor–ApoE interaction or after losing apolipoprotein B-100—and subsequent conversion into LDL through hepatic lipase-driven remodeling. Together, these represent complete physiological handling mechanisms responsible for removing IDL from plasma. 

